{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6d40432-06d8-43ed-bd99-6275211d4baa","content":"This is a **TUnit** project (uses MTP natively). TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` syntax, not VSTest `--filter`. The command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nThis glob-style tree node filter matches the `SmsNotificationTests` class at any depth and includes all tests within it (`SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62ac39fa-d020-469a-ac0b-0dd9792b4318","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit with MTP, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit on MTP, the filter uses `--treenode-filter` syntax. To filter by class name, the syntax would be:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"\n```\n\nLet me make sure about TUnit's filter syntax. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform, and its filter is `--treenode-filter` with a path-like syntax.\n\nThe treenode filter for TUnit uses a hierarchical path: `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Method`\n\n\nTo filter by class, I can use either `--treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"` for a more explicit path structure or `--treenode-filter \"/**/SmsNotificationTests/**\"` with glob patterns to match the class and its methods.","outputTokens":406,"requestId":"4808:1F56EA:84ACDB:98DF00:69FBEAB8"},"id":"03aec675-ab54-48ab-bf45-c46dcfbcadae","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:28:34.403Z","parentId":"2e9e4dfa-f597-456b-9551-a7ca6fc0fa10"}
